  "type": "spr",
  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">In the given equation, <span class=\"italic\">k</span> is a constant. If the equation has infinitely many solutions, what is the value of <span class=\"italic\">k</span> ?</p>\n",
  "answerOptions": [],
  "keys": [],
  "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is 5. Subtracting <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"6 x\"></span> from both sides of the given equation gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"k equals 5\"></span>, so for any value of <span class=\"italic\">x</span>, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"6 x plus k, equals, 6 x plus 5 \"></span> if and only if <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"k equals 5\"></span>. Therefore, if the given equation has infinitely many solutions, the value of <span class=\"italic\">k</span> is 5.</p>\n",
